{"TopicId":179627,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Multiple Gravity Assists/Delta V","CreatedByName":"PTGFlyer","CreatedById":155676,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T04:10:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"PTGFlyer","CreatedById":155676,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T04:10:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow does one determine if\u00A0planets are lined up\u00A0for multiple gravitational assists? And on a related note, how do you determine how much delta V you gain from an\u00A0assist?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-08T04:12:35Z\u0022 title=\u002211/08/2018 04:12  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 8, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by PTGFlyer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T06:15:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis thread appeared very recently (even though it\u0027s about \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E, the answers apply to stock as well)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2970209019\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179531-what-mod-can-i-use-to-plan-a-transfer-window-with-a-gravity-assist-for-rss/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3481595\u0026amp;embedComment=3481595\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-3481595\u0022 style=\u0022height:318px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are tools to calculate transfer windows for chosen gravity assists, as well as Delta-v for any potential burns etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd let me tell ya, it saves a lot of fuel, but of course cost more time. For my Cassini recreation (OPM Sarnus) my mission time increased by two years but I saved a lot of fuel thanks to Jool and Sarnus\u0027 moons assists.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PTGFlyer","CreatedById":155676,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T12:58:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks. Didn\u2019t see that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}